data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fn26.com\u002Fes-es\u002Fblog\u002Fpagar-impuestos-autonomos-en-espana-con-n26-business"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"underline"}],"value":"artículo","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" en donde te explicamos todos los detalles.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"document"},"fr":{"data":{},"content":[],"nodeType":"document"},"it":{"data":{},"content":[],"nodeType":"document"},"pt":{"data":{},"content":[],"nodeType":"document"}},"content":{"en":[{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Entry","id":"4Tb5f0ixkpBjSEDzve7rIw"}}]},"seoData":{"en":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Entry","id":"4CvRxHOX2mGph2eyX3U6Jw"}}}}}}}},{"metadata":{"tags":[]},"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"q33z48p65a6w"}},"id":"6qBq7YrQO1hAmuR2pk84c2","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-04-16T10:28:07.914Z","updatedAt":"2021-04-16T10:28:07.914Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"redirect"}}},"fields":{"from":{"en":"crm-phishing-fr"},"toCountry":{"en":[{"metadata":{"tags":[]},"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"q33z48p65a6w"}},"id":"6rukBRntfcu03D0Xfd1gDN","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-04-16T09:38:02.285Z","updatedAt":"2021-04-16T10:15:12.151Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"blogPost"}}},"fields":{"internalTitle":{"en":"Blogpost - How to detect scams (FR)"},"countryCodes":{"en":["FR"]},"title":{"en":"Financial scams—how to identify and avoid fraud","fr":"Escroquerie et arnaque financière : comment les reconnaître ?"},"slug":{"en":"how-to-spot-online-scams-and-fraud","fr":"escroquerie-et-arnaque-financiere-comment-les-reconnaitre"},"previewImage":{"en":{"metadata":{"tags":[{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Tag","id":"asset1NoApp"}},{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Tag","id":"asset2Other"}}]},"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"q33z48p65a6w"}},"id":"5inEKu8LpgguwXobzBPzOn","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2021-04-16T09:32:36.681Z","updatedAt":"2021-06-05T09:31:03.726Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2},"fields":{"title":{"en":" How to detect scams ","fr":"Comment détecter les escroqueries"},"description":{"en":"Hands on a keyboard","fr":"Des mains sur un clavier"},"file":{"en":{"url":"\u002F\u002Fimages.ctfassets.net\u002Fq33z48p65a6w\u002F5inEKu8LpgguwXobzBPzOn\u002F61b848168007ab4f4c2ad277e288a005\u002Fdamian-zaleski-RYyr-k3Ysqg-unsplash.jpg","details":{"size":884173,"image":{"width":3588,"height":1842}},"fileName":"damian-zaleski-RYyr-k3Ysqg-unsplash.jpg","contentType":"image\u002Fjpeg"},"fr":{"url":"\u002F\u002Fimages.ctfassets.net\u002Fq33z48p65a6w\u002F5inEKu8LpgguwXobzBPzOn\u002F457576ad3752da80d33ae5675a66c635\u002Fdamian-zaleski-RYyr-k3Ysqg-unsplash.jpg","details":{"size":884173,"image":{"width":3588,"height":1842}},"fileName":"damian-zaleski-RYyr-k3Ysqg-unsplash.jpg","contentType":"image\u002Fjpeg"}}}}},"categoryId":{"en":"technology"},"category":{"en":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Entry","id":"kaFaEXjWLYmWEIi4wGi2I"}}},"date":{"en":"2021-04-16"},"excerpt":{"en":"Learn how to spot scams and keep your bank account safe from fraudsters—both online and offline.","fr":"Découvrez dans cet article comment reconnaître et vous protéger des arnaques et escroqueries."},"copy":{"en":{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Since the start of the pandemic, many of us have spent long hours connected to our computers and cellphones. While some forms of crime have decreased during lockdown, others have unfortunately become more prevalent, including online scams and fraud. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\n","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Be vigilant—learn to spot fraudulent phone calls and emails","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Due to the global pandemic, the number of fraud attempts has exploded. The uncertain economic context, health concerns, lockdown restrictions, and the explosion of online commerce are all factors that may have contributed to the massive increase in online and phone-based scams. You can find ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fn26.com\u002Fen-eu\u002Fblog\u002Fonline-security-guide"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"underline"}],"value":"a guide to online safety","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" on our blog, but read on to get an overview of financial scams and how to spot them.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\n","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"What is the purpose of fraudulent emails and phone calls?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"The goal of fraudsters is simple—they want to steal your money. To do this, they try to get you to invest in fake financial products in order to gain access to your bank account details, or to transfer them money. But just like phishing attempts, financial scams can also be aimed at retrieving your personal information.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"What are the most common types of scams?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"There are various types of common financial scams. Here’s a roundup of information from the ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.abe-infoservice.fr\u002Fvos-demarches\u002Fse-proteger-contre-les-arnaques\u002Fles-mises-en-garde-des-autorites\u002Fattention-aux-arnaques-financieres\u002Fles-differents-types-darnaques-financieres#3"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Assurance Banque Epargne Information platform","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":", set up by the Banque de France, the ACPR (Prudential Control and Resolution Authority), and the AMF (Financial Markets Authority). ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Fraudulent saving opportunities","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Offering so-called “savings products” is a common scam, where someone gets in touch to offer you a unique investment opportunity. They’ll likely contain suspicious conditions, such as “guaranteed” exceedingly high interest rates of up to 15%. Investments may also be presented as “risk-free”. The goal here is to gain access to your personal information, or to get you to pay large sums of money to the fraudster directly. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Investment scams","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Investment scams are varied and often involve financial investments with very high rates of return. Fraudersts may assume the identity of a viable financial institution, or suggest alternative investments in atypical goods or precious materials, for example. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Fraudulent credit offers","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Some fraudsters may contact you with an offer for a loan with conditions that you would never expect from a real bank or credit institution—think low rates, very long repayment periods, and no conditions. Fraudsters who offer this type of loan often offer quick repayment.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"First, they’ll likely ask you for a first payment to cover supposed costs. Once the transfer is made, they’ll take the money and run. \n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Impersonation, falsifying identity, and identity theft","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"More and more scams involve someone impersonating a bank or a financial institution to offer fake products, often going so far as to fraudulently use the identity of the bank’s actual employees to reach out to their victims by telephone and by email. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"In some cases, the fraudster will pretend to be an employee from an institution or an administrative body—such as the CAF or Pole Emploi. These fraudsters may attempt to steal your identity after they collect your personal information, then make transfers or take out loans in your name once they gain access to your bank accounts.\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Here's how to recognize attempted fraud","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"When reading your emails or answering your phone, here are a few red flags to watch out for:\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Someone posing as N26 or another bank that offers you financial services by email or phone","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Emails or phone calls that offer very profitable financial products, such as exceptionally high interest rates","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"A company or an individual contacts you to recommend a third party, who supposedly has investment expertise","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Someone claims that you're one of a selected few to be offered an attractive financial service","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Someone contacts you to request your bank details and other personal information, or the payment of a lump sum of money","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"You’re informed that whatever financial product you’re being offered is approved by some public authority","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"You’re told that your bank or credit institution requires you to sign a new contract following a name change on their end","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Basically, if it sounds too good to be true, it probably is.\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Tools you can use to detect possible scams","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\nThe French authorities have provided a list of trusted organizations that allow you to check whether the person contacting you is authorized to offer financial services such as savings or credit. Among them are the REGAFI, ORIAS, and the GECO database. All these sites and databases list approved establishments. For atypical investments, the Autorité des Marchés Financiers (AMF) also provides a ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.amf-france.org\u002Ffr\u002Fespace-epargnants\u002Fproteger-son-epargne\u002Flistes-blanches"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"white list of approved bodies","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":".","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Furthermore, French authorities also publish a ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.abe-infoservice.fr\u002Fliste-noire\u002Flistes-noires-et-alertes-des-autorites"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"blacklist of establishments and published alerts of fraud attempts","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":", as do ABEIS and AMF.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Beware of any fraudsters posing as N26","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"At N26, your account security is our highest priority, and we go to great measures to protect our customers every step of the way. However, like many banks or financial institutions, we are sometimes confronted with fraud attempts.\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"The techniques used by fraudsters are more and more sophisticated, and it can sometimes be difficult to detect fake emails, texts, and phone calls. This is particularly true when fraudsters impersonate trusted financial institutions as part of their scam.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\nHere are some things to keep in mind that can help you to avoid malicious attacks: ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"N26 will never contact you by email or phone to personally sell you financial products","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"You can only sign up to N26 products via the mobile N26 app, or the N26 WebApp","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"—we’ll never ask you to sign up via phone, mail, or email","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"To date, N26 doesn’t offer any investment products or savings accounts in France","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"How should I react to a fraud attempt?","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"If you receive a fraudulent phone call, don’t answer any questions or give out your personal information, and hang up. If you receive a suspicious email, never click on any of the links  if you have the slightest bit of doubt about its authenticity.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"If you are approached by someone who claims to be an N26 employee, or if you receive a suspicious email or SMS from N26, please contact Customer Support right away. You can contact N26 Customer Support via your N26 app, or the N26 WebApp. If you’re not an N26 customer, you can also get in touch with us via the live-chat function available via our ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.n26.com\u002Fen-fr"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"underline"}],"value":"Support Center","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":".","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"What to do if you’re a victim of fraudulent emails or phone calls","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"If you think you’ve received a fraudulent email or phone call, we recommend reporting it on the Ministry of the Interior’s website. You can find more information ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.demarches.interieur.gouv.fr\u002Fparticuliers\u002Fescroquerie"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"here","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":". If you’ve been the victim of a scam or financial fraud, please report it right away. To do so, go to the government website: https:\u002F\u002Fwww.pre-plainte-en-ligne.gouv.fr\u002F.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"You can also contact “Info Escroqueries”, a free hotline in France dedicated to fraud and scams. The number is 0805805807 and they’re available Monday to Friday from 9:00 am to 6:30 pm CET. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[],"nodeType":"hr"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"To learn more about online security and how to protect yourself, check out the ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fn26.com\u002Fen-eu\u002Fblog\u002Fcategory\u002Ftechnology"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Technology & Security","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" section of our blog.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\n\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"document"},"fr":{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Depuis le début de la pandémie, nous sommes nombreux à passer de longues heures connectés à nos ordinateurs ou à nos téléphones portables. S’ils s’est avéré que certaines formes de criminalité ou de délits ont reculé, d’autres ont bondi et parmi eux, les arnaques ou escroqueries. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Arnaques et escroqueries en ligne et par téléphone : voici autant de formes de fraudes auxquelles nous souhaitons vous sensibiliser. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Escroquerie, arnaque en ligne, mail frauduleux : faites preuve de vigilance","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Avec la pandémie, l’escroquerie a définitivement pris une nouvelle dimension et le nombre d’arnaques en ligne explose. Le contexte économique incertain, l’inquiétude des populations face à la crise, les restrictions sanitaires ou encore l’explosion du commerce en ligne sont autant de facteurs qui ont pu contribuer à l’augmentation massive des tentatives d’escroquerie. Nous avons déjà publié un ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fn26.com\u002Ffr-fr\u002Fblog\u002Fguide-securite-en-ligne"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"underline"}],"value":"guide de la sécurité en ligne","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" sur notre blog mais nous souhaitons aujourd’hui vous parler plus en détail des escroqueries. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Quel est le but de l’escroquerie ou de l’arnaque ? ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"L’escroc qui cherche à vous arnaquer a généralement pour objectif de vous faire investir dans un produit financier fictif pour détourner votre argent. Mais tout comme les tentatives de ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"phishing","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":", l’escroquerie financière peut aussi viser à récupérer vos informations personnelles ou à accéder à vos identifiants bancaires. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Quelles types d’escroquerie ou d'arnaque sont les plus répandues ?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\nAujourd’hui, nous souhaitons vous sensibiliser à certains types d’escroquerie ou d’arnaque financière, telles que répertoriées par la plateforme ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.abe-infoservice.fr\u002Fvos-demarches\u002Fse-proteger-contre-les-arnaques\u002Fles-mises-en-garde-des-autorites\u002Fattention-aux-arnaques-financieres\u002Fles-differents-types-darnaques-financieres#3"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"underline"}],"value":"Assurance Banque Epargne Info ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.abe-infoservice.fr\u002Fvos-demarches\u002Fse-proteger-contre-les-arnaques\u002Fles-mises-en-garde-des-autorites\u002Fattention-aux-arnaques-financieres\u002Fles-differents-types-darnaques-financieres#3"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"underline"}],"value":"Service","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":", mise en place par la Banque de France, l’ACPR (Autorité de contrôle prudentiel et de résolution) et l’AMF (Autorité des marchés financiers) :\n","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Les offres d’épargne frauduleuses","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Les démarchages pour vous proposer de prétendus produits d’épargne sont fréquents et consistent à proposer des livrets d’épargne aux taux d’intérêts très élevés, les promesses pouvant aller jusqu’à 15 % “garantis” et présentés “sans aucun risque” pour l’épargnant. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Une fois de plus, les informations personnelles sont souvent dérobées et dès les premières sommes d’argent versées (parfois très importantes), l’escroc disparaît avec le butin de son arnaque. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Les arnaques financières ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Les arnaques financières sont variées et concernent souvent des placements financiers aux taux de rentabilité extrêmement élevés, des versements avec la promesse d’un remboursement futur auprès de sociétés dont l’identité est usurpée, des placements alternatifs dans des biens atypiques ou des matières précieuses, par exemple.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Les offres de crédit frauduleuses","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Ce type d’escroquerie vise à proposer une offre de crédit à des taux très avantageux et dans des conditions que personne ne pourrait trouver auprès d’une véritable banque ou établissement de crédit : taux faibles qui ne varient pas selon le montant du prêt, durée de remboursement très longue, sans conditions imposées. Les escrocs qui proposent ce type de crédit proposent souvent un versement rapide de la somme empruntée. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Souvent, la personne victime de l’escroquerie se voit demander un premier versement pour couvrir des frais supposés et une fois la somme virée, l’escroc disparaît. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"\n","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Ces fraudes sont de plus en plus accompagnées d’usurpations d’identité ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-4"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"De plus en plus de fraudes impliquent l’","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"usurpation de l’identité d’une banque ou d’un établissement financier ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"pour vous proposer de faux produits en allant même souvent jusqu'à  utiliser l'identité de ses employés pour effectuer des démarchages par téléphone et par email ;","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Dans certains cas, les escrocs peuvent","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":" usurper l’identité d’une autori