,{"metadata":{"tags":[]},"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"q33z48p65a6w"}},"id":"7o50JoTV1YK0vntx3tA4pu","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-10-12T07:49:30.570Z","updatedAt":"2020-10-12T07:49:30.570Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"redirect"}}},"fields":{"from":{"en":"\u002Fen-eu\u002Fwhat-cash-costs-businesses"},"to":{"en":{"metadata":{"tags":[{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Tag","id":"blog1Evergreen"}},{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Tag","id":"blog2TechnologySecurity"}},{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Tag","id":"blog3Global"}},{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Tag","id":"blog4NoConversionCard"}}]},"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"q33z48p65a6w"}},"id":"3WKDTALe5qyEwI4MCs46Yw","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-04-26T14:00:49.307Z","updatedAt":"2021-06-25T10:10:26.738Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":11,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"blogPost"}}},"fields":{"internalTitle":{"de":"Was uns Bargeld kostet","en":"The Cost of Cash"},"countryCodes":{"en":["DE","AT","EU","GB"]},"title":{"de":"Die Kosten von Bargeld","en":"The cost of cash"},"slug":{"de":"was-uns-bargeld-kostet","en":"the-cost-of-cash"},"previewImage":{"en":{"metadata":{"tags":[{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Tag","id":"asset1NoApp"}},{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Tag","id":"asset2Other"}}]},"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"q33z48p65a6w"}},"id":"3Ypdzzl17yWUS8Ya0cCCG","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-03-04T11:10:43.142Z","updatedAt":"2021-06-05T09:26:57.382Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3},"fields":{"title":{"de":"Was uns Bargeld kostet","en":"The Cost of Cash"},"description":{"de":"Dollar-Scheine","en":"Dollar bills","es":"Billetes de dólar","fr":"Billets d'un dollar","it":"Banconote da un dollaro"},"file":{"de":{"url":"\u002F\u002Fimages.ctfassets.net\u002Fq33z48p65a6w\u002F3Ypdzzl17yWUS8Ya0cCCG\u002F3c574e1a1e410ba184058989cdf6c4e3\u002FiStock_000006841434_Large.jpg","details":{"size":1660597,"image":{"width":1280,"height":853}},"fileName":"iStock_000006841434_Large.jpg","contentType":"image\u002Fjpeg"},"en":{"url":"\u002F\u002Fimages.ctfassets.net\u002Fq33z48p65a6w\u002F3Ypdzzl17yWUS8Ya0cCCG\u002F3c902e1baf9907f3ce5efe67d1ed42ef\u002FiStock_000006841434_Large.jpg","details":{"size":1660597,"image":{"width":1280,"height":853}},"fileName":"iStock_000006841434_Large.jpg","contentType":"image\u002Fjpeg"}}}}},"categoryId":{"en":"technology"},"category":{"en":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Entry","id":"kaFaEXjWLYmWEIi4wGi2I"}}},"date":{"en":"2016-02-04"},"excerpt":{"de":"Bargeld kostet unglaublich viel und ermöglicht viele illegale Aktivitäten erst überhaupt. Wir erklären, warum Bargeld immer seltener wird. ","en":"Why does cash cost so much money? We explain the cost of cash and why cashless payments are the future. "},"copy":{"de":{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Trends beweisen: der Gebrauch von Bargeld wird immer weniger. Die meisten Vorhersagen der nächsten Jahrzehnte unterstreichen diese Hypothese nur. Die Europäische Zentralbank hat bestätigt, dass der 500 € - Schein auslaufen wird. Und wir begrüßen diesen Trend, nicht weil wir persönlich etwas gegen Bargeld haben, sondern weil Bargeld so ein schwieriges Mittel ist. Es kostet unglaublich viel Geld und ermöglicht viele illegale Aktivitäten erst überhaupt. Langfristig glauben wir, dass die Wirtschaft oder Gesellschaft generell auf Bargeld verzichten wird. Aber warum?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Gesamtwirtschaftliche Kosten","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Bargeld muss gedruckt, überprüft, transportiert und sichergestellt werden. Das kostet die deutsche Wirtschaft jährlich über 10 Milliarden Euro. Dabei sind noch nicht alle illegalen Aktivitäten berücksichtigt und ganz ehrlich, wie oft habt ihr schon einen 500 € - Schein verwendet?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Individuelle Kosten","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Nicht nur die Wirtschaft oder Geschäfte zahlen für Bargeld, sondern auch Privatpersonen. Jedes Jahr werden astronomische Summen an Bargeld gestohlen oder einfach verloren. Auf Bargeld gibt es außerdem so gut wie keine Zinsen, es zahlt sich also auch nicht als Investition aus. Und: Zeit ist Geld. All die Minuten in Schlangen vor Geldautomaten oder an der Supermarktkasse während die Person vor euch einzelne Münzen zählt sind wertvolle Minuten eurer Zeit.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Versteckte Kosten","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Die versteckten Kosten von Bargeld belaufen sich auf knapp 150 € pro Person im Jahr. Vieles davon geht an Banken – für Sicherheitssysteme, Geldautomatenwartung und so weiter. Umgewandelt sind das für Kunden nämlich die Kontoführungsgebühren.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Mit der N26 App könnt ihr eure Karte jetzt noch viel effizienter und besser verwenden als Bargeld.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Mit Push-Nachrichten in Echtzeit, der automatischen Kategorisierung und eingebauten Statistiken, könnt ihr jederzeit erkennen wo ihr euer Geld wie ausgebt und behaltet viel besser den Überblick als mit Bargeld. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Deutschland hinkt hinterher","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"In Deutschland sind Kartenzahlungen aber noch immer weit weniger verbreitet als in anderen Ländern. Wenn wir einen kurzen Blick in den Norden nach Schweden werfen, könnten wir viel lernen. Schweden zahlen fünf Mal mehr mit Karten als Deutsche. Zwischen 2010 und 2012 sind mehr als 500 schwedische Bankfilialen komplett auf bargeldlose Zahlungen umgestiegen. Die Regierung dort will bis 2030 komplett bargeldlos sein. Münzen und Scheine werden sogar im öffentlichen Verkehr immer mehr zur Rarität.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Wie könnt ihr auf Bargeld verzichten?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Zückt doch auch mal für kleinere Zahlungen die Karte. Im Durchschnitt zahlen Deutsche erst ab Beträgen über 60 € mit der Karte, aber das hat keinen ökonomischen Mehrwert. Studien belegen, dass es sich finanziell auszahlt Beträge ab 6 € bereits mit der Karte zu bezahlen.\nUnd in vielen Ländern weltweit wäre das die Norm. Seit Juni 2015 sind Taxis auch dazu verpflichtet Kartenzahlungen zu akzeptieren und Geschäfte müssen in der Regel drei verschiedene Kartentypen akzeptieren. Bei großen Ketten wie Lidl und Aldi steigt die Anzahl der Kartenzahlungen seit 2015 stets. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Lasst uns gemeinsam Banking verändern!","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"document"},"en":{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Whether in the context of politics or business, cash seems to be on the way out. You’d be hard-pressed to find many forecasters who see a growing financial future for paper bills or copper coins. One clear signal: the European Central Bank will be discontinuing the €500 note. It’s not personal. It’s not that we have a “thing” against cash. We’d probably even be friends, if cash didn’t make having a relationship so difficult. It’s expensive to process and it enables sketchy activities. We just don’t see a long-term future with it for the economy in general or for modern banking in particular. Sorry, cash. But why does cash cost so much money?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Macroeconomic costs","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Cash needs to be printed, continually inspected and then transported to and secured in safes. That costs the German economy over €10 billion each year. That’s not to mention all the illegal activity in Germany associated with cash (think about it—have you ever used a €500 bill?) ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Individual costs","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"It’s not just the macro economy or business service providers that pay the price for cash; individuals pay as well. Every year astronomical sums of cash are lost or stolen. These days, cash often earns essentially no interest, meaning it’s a non-productive investment vehicle. And finally, think of all the time spent\u002F lost productivity from standing in lines at ATMs or waiting for slow cash transactions at a retailer.  ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Hidden costs","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"It’s estimated that the hidden cost of cash has soared to more than €150 annually per German citizen. Much of this is initially borne by banks—for security, ATM maintenance, etc.—but then often comes back to bite consumers. This is why most banks charge for conventional checking accounts, impose minimum deposit requirements, or both.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"The N26 app gives you the power to use your card in ways that are much better than cash","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Spending control:","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" Some people are concerned about “losing control” of spending by using a card. But the truth is that using cash is probably the least trackable way to spend money. The statistics in the N26 app show you detailed breakdowns of exactly where you’ve used your card, so you stay in the know.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Purchase confirmation:","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" Ever feel uncertain about whether the correct amount will be booked after a card purchase? With N26 you’ll receive an instant push notification after every card usage, so you can always be sure.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Small amounts:","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" If you find it cumbersome to make bank transfers for small amounts (say, €3.50 to your friend for a beer), our MoneyBeam feature can help. With MoneyBeam you can instantly transfer funds to friends. It’s even faster than grabbing money out of your wallet, really.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Germany is lagging behind","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Germans are still a bit critical when it comes to card payments. The leaders in Europe are the Swedes. By looking to our friends up north, we can see just how much potential there is in card payments.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Swedes pay five times more often with cards compared to Germans. From 2010 to 2012 more than 500 Swedish bank branches completely switched to cashless operation. The government’s goal is to be 100% cashless by 2030. Coins and bills are disappearing as a payment option on local public transport.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"So, what are some suggestions for a glorious world that’s free from cash?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Consider using your card even for smaller amounts. On average, Germans tend to reach for a card only once purchases reach €60 or so (which is already getting quite sizeable, in our opinion). But really, there’s no good reason for that. Studies show that there is a macroeconomic benefit to pay by card for amounts one tenth of that, or more like €6. And in many countries in the world, that would be completely normal. Since June 2015 taxis are required to accept card payments—in fact, each business needs to accept a minimum of three of the traditional cards. In the big-box discount stores like Lidl and Aldi, the trend towards card payments has been growing since the summer of 2015.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Visit the ATM less often. Every ATM transaction pumps expensive cash back into circulation to start the long cycle again.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"And ok...self-serving as this may be...please share your enthusiasm for N26 with friends and family. With our fast account sign-up process, you’ll be able to share MoneyBeams with them before you know it.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Let’s change banking together!","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"document"},"es":{"data":{},"content":[],"nodeType":"document"},"fr":{"data":{},"content":[],"nodeType":"document"},"it":{"data":{},"content":[],"nodeType":"document"},"pt":{"data":{},"content":[],"nodeType":"document"}},"content":{"en":[{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Entry","id":"6iKKCkzsKcCT6yxDYNhu3y"}}]},"seoData":{"en":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Entry","id":"2xvoEWNrLdS731iGhpfiN6"}}}}}}}},{"metadata":{"tags":[]},"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"q33z48p65a6w"}},"id":"tF4kMZIjBZ9poGIQF674H","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-10-12T07:40:35.666Z","updatedAt":"2020-10-12T07:40:35.666Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"redirect"}}},"fields":{"from":{"en":"\u002Fen-es\u002Fbusiness-black-launch"},"to":{"en":{"metadata":{"tags":[]},"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"q33z48p65a6w"}},"id":"6SHsHg2HeMASmeKkk2UUou","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-05T07:26:02.266Z","updatedAt":"2021-05-11T16:51:06.311Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"blogPost"}}},"fields":{"internalTitle":{"en":"Blog: Business Black Launch (DE, AT, FR, IT, ES)"},"countryCodes":{"en":["DE","AT","FR","IT","ES"]},"title":{"de":"N26 Business Black ist da! Euer Büro, wo immer ihr seid","en":"Your office, wherever you are: introducing N26 Business Black","es":"Tu oficina, donde quiera que estés. Presentamos N26 Business Black.","fr":"Avec le nouveau compte N26 Business Black, partez en voyage professionnel en toute sérénité","it":"La tua attività, sempre con te, ovunque tu sia. È arrivata N26 Business Black"},"slug":{"de":"business-black-ist-da","en":"business-black-launch","es":"lanzamiento-business-black","fr":"lancement-business-black","it":"lancio-busines